TITLE: Europe's Stripe rival Adyen dives 39% after slowest sales growth on record
SUMMARY: Adyen reported revenue of 739.1 million euros ($804.3 million) in the first half of the year, up by 21% from 2022, but below analyst estimates.

TITLE: Walmart raises full-year earnings forecast as grocery, online growth fuel higher sales
SUMMARY: Walmart beat earnings and revenue expectations as it capitalizes on its low-priced reputation with consumers looking for value.

TITLE: Shoppers are spending big at T.J. Maxx, HomeGoods as Target sales slide
SUMMARY: TJX Cos., which runs T.J. Maxx and Marshalls, is seeing big gains in discretionary purchases as cash-strapped consumers look for a deal amid high inflation.

TITLE: Target slashes full-year earnings forecast as retailer struggles to win over thrifty shoppers
SUMMARY: Target cut its full-year forecast even as recession fears fade, as the retailer cited factors like still high prices and the restart of student loan payments.

TITLE: HKEX first-half net profit rises 31%, CEO is 'quite optimistic' about medium term outlook
SUMMARY: Hong Kong Exchanges and Clearing reported a 31% year-on-year rise in net profit for the first six months of the year.

TITLE: China's Tencent misses expectations despite fastest profit rise since late 2021
SUMMARY: Tencent on Wednesday reported a surge in profit for the second quarter, but missed expectations.

TITLE: Cava shares surge as Mediterranean restaurant chain swings to a profit in first report since IPO
SUMMARY: Cava net sales soared 62% to $172.9 million, fueled by new restaurant openings.

TITLE: Home Depot beats earnings estimates, but sales slide as consumers pull back on big-ticket buys
SUMMARY: Home Depot beat earnings estimates but reiterated its full-year guidance, saying consumers are still wary of big-ticket purchases.

TITLE: Chinese tech giant Huawei reports tepid consumer revenue growth for the first half of 2023
SUMMARY: Huawei on Friday reported 2.2% year-on-year growth in its consumer business revenue for the first half of the year.

TITLE: SMIC posted a drop in second-quarter revenue on persisting weak chip demand
SUMMARY: SMIC posted a drop in second-quarter revenue amid ongoing U.S. sanctions and a sluggish recovery in global chip demand.

TITLE: Alibaba reports solid earnings beat, revenue rises most since Sept. 2021
SUMMARY: Chinese e-commerce giant Alibaba's U.S.-traded shares rose by 4.5% in premarket trading after it released results.

TITLE: Viasat revenue grows as investigation continues into malfunctioning $750 million satellite
SUMMARY: Viasat reportedly quarterly results on Wednesday as the company continues to investigate its recent satellite malfunction.

TITLE: Disney posts mixed results for quarter plagued by streaming woes, restructuring costs
SUMMARY: Subscriber losses continued over the last three months, with the company reporting 146.1 million Disney+ subscribers, a 7.4% decline.

TITLE: Roblox shares drop 21% after company misses estimates on top and bottom line
SUMMARY: Roblox reported its second-quarter results Wednesday.

TITLE: Sony raises forecast on PlayStation gaming growth but profit drops 31% in first quarter
SUMMARY: Sony on Wednesday reported a 31% fall in profit in the June quarter — but raised full-year sales forecasts on the back of strength in its PlayStation business.

TITLE: Rocket Lab results match Wall Street estimates, company adds contracts for 10 launches
SUMMARY: Rocket Lab reported second-quarter results on Tuesday that largely met Wall Street's expectations.

TITLE: Rivian raises 2023 EV production guidance, posts narrower-than-expected quarterly loss
SUMMARY: Rivian now expects to build about 52,000 vehicles in 2023, more than twice the number it made in 2022.

TITLE: Novavax posts surprise quarterly profit as company prepares to launch new Covid vaccine
SUMMARY: Novavax is working to strengthen its financial position after it raised doubts about its ability to stay in business earlier this year.

TITLE: Restaurant Brands' sales rise, fueled by Burger King and Tim Hortons growth
SUMMARY: Burger King and Tim Hortons both reported double-digit same-store sales growth.

TITLE: Eli Lilly raises full-year guidance as Mounjaro, other drugs drive second-quarter profit up 85%
SUMMARY: Eli Lilly's stock has been on a tear, driven by positive trial results for its Alzheimer's drug and progress with its promising obesity drug pipeline.

TITLE: SoftBank posts surprise loss even as Vision Fund back in black after five quarters
SUMMARY: SoftBank surprised the market with a loss in the first quarter, though its Vision Fund booked a $1.1 billion gain on investments — its first in five quarters.

TITLE: Space company Redwire trims quarterly losses, builds order backlog past $270 million
SUMMARY: Space infrastructure company Redwire reported second-quarter results Monday, as it nearly erased its net losses.

TITLE: Palantir reports 13% revenue growth, issues guidance that tops estimates
SUMMARY: Palantir executives say revenue growth will accelerate in the third quarter, reversing a trend from the last several years.

TITLE: Paramount to sell Simon & Schuster to KKR for $1.62 billion; media giant's earnings top estimates
SUMMARY: Paramount Global has agreed to sell Simon & Schuster to private equity giant KKR for $1.62 billion, the company said as it reported quarterly earnings.

TITLE: Lucid misses revenue expectations after EV deliveries disappoint
SUMMARY: Lucid's second-quarter revenue fell short of expectations, but a recent cash raise extended the EV maker's runway into 2025.

TITLE: EVgo revenue beats analyst expectations as private-label charging business booms
SUMMARY: EVgo's second-quarter results beat Wall Street estimates, as revenue from deals to provide chargers to other businesses surged.

TITLE: Qualcomm sales and forecast come up light as smartphone chip sales fall 25%
SUMMARY: Qualcomm is exposed to the slumping smartphone industry because it makes the processors at the heart of most high-end Android devices.

TITLE: Humana shares rise after insurer's medical costs came in lower than expected
SUMMARY: The results ease investor concerns after Humana and rival UnitedHealth Group warned of a surge in demand for nonurgent surgeries and outpatient services.

TITLE: Taco Bell owner Yum Brands misses revenue estimates despite soaring KFC sales
SUMMARY: Yum Brands restaurant KFC's same-store sales climbed 13%, fueled by demand in China, its largest market.

TITLE: CVS beats on earnings and revenue as the company slashes costs
SUMMARY: CVS is cutting costs as it pushes deeper into health-care services after its acquisitions of Signify Health and Oak Street Health.
